Defendant Robert Scott Clyburn in court with attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub.  Defendant Robert Scott Clyburn in custody.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
AS TO COUNT  1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 11 YEARS, CONCURRENT with Counts 2, 3, and 5, CONSECUTIVE to other time that may be served, with credit for 134 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 5 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 6 YEARS.

AS TO COUNT 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 11 YEARS, CONCURRENT with Counts 1, 3, and 5, CONSECUTIVE to any other time that may be served, with credit for 134 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 5 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 6 YEARS.

AS TO COUNT 3:  Defendant sentenced to 9 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, Concurrent with Counts 1, 2, and 5 with credit for 134 days, Consecutive to any other time that may be served.

AS TO COUNT  5:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 8 YEARS, CONCURRENT with Counts 1, 2, and 3, CONSECUTIVE to other time that may be served, with credit for 134 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 4 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 4 YEARS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program AFTER SERVING THE FIRST 3 YEARS OF THIS SENTENCE.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain mental health assessment if not previously done so- successfully complete follow-up treatment and programming ;
*Take any and all prescription medication only in the manner/dosage as prescribed by a treating physician;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Cooperate with random urine screens;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with victims Matthew P., Laura N., Timothy G., Habtemariam T. Charles G. and Great Clips located at 10280 W. National Ave.; as to Charles G only, agent given discretion to lift no contact order as it was not requested by the victim;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*As to all counts- Pay victim/witness surcharge and all other mandatory applicable fees, assessments, and costs; 

The state in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution in the following stipulated amounts: $585.00 payable to Great Clips located at 10280 W. National Ave, $753.87 payable to Matthew P., $1985.96 to Progressive Universal Insurance Co., $3668.79 payable to Walgreens located at 9100 W. Beloit Ave.  The Court orders restitution to be before court ordered costs with Matthew P. being paid first.  The Court orders Great Clips, Progressive Universal Insurance, and Walgreens to be paid on a proportionate basis.   The Court ordered that all financial obligations and restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Appeal rights given by the court.
